<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Debug::dump() bug:</p>

<p>if data in variable not in utf-8, its striped by htmlentities</p>

<p>bug:</p>

<p>Debug.php @ 93 line</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
htmlentities($output, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8')
</code></pre>

<p>fix:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
htmlspecialchars($output, ENT_QUOTES)
</code></pre>

<p>Why?
1) Data can be not only utf-8 encoding
2) if you are using ENT_QUOTES, you dont need htmlentities ;-)</p>

